the thing with pets is timing.. you have to time your remez and they have to time their backoff command to hit at the smae time..  It can be very frustrating.  I only let them die when they make no attempt to back their pet off.  Yes pets sometimes just go bonkers (whether it be bad targeting or sometimes I think they just get a mind of their own) but as long as the pet owner is trying to work with you then your okay (a stun, coupled with a pet back off command and a quick mez works 85% of the time)<P>The thing with 2nd, 3rd, 4rth, etc. characters.. twinks or not, is that they are usually willing to take more risks (especially if your twinked) and it can be hard to determine what your classes limits are.  Personally, my twinks I usually play solo or with a few other friends.
